HEADWORD: orthodontics
<hw>orthodontics</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A branch of
dentistry specializing in the treatment of the teeth so as to make the
teeth align properly within the mouth; it usually involves fitting a
patient with braces and sometimes oral surgery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

